🎥 🎞️ @clickclickjim⁠⁠⁠

node.text:
@johnwardlearchitects gallery-like home is filled with impeccable crafts and art archive as an eclectic memoir of celebrated Australian architect’s adventures from childhood to now.

A film by @cocoandmaximilian. 
Music by @elliotcfmunn. 

See the full feature on yellowtrace.com.au.

#YellowtraceResidential
#YellowtraceInAus

node.text:
@dana.tomic.hughes had the pleasure of chatting with the mega talented @philippemalouin about his practice, the importance of design mentoring, staying true to yourself and the future of design. Philippe was recently involved with mentoring the finalists of #LexusDesignAward. Find out more at @discoverlexus, and keep an eye out for the Grand Prix winner announcement on September 1st ✌🏼
#YellowtraceInterviews #YellowtracePartner #TeamYellowtrace

node.text:
Since establishing @richardsandspence in 2008, Ingrid Richards and Adrian Spence have changed the face of their home city with world-class retail, hospitality and civic architecture. Here they open up their own bangin' home in Brisbane's Bowen Hills, which flips the idea of a typical house on its head 🙌🏼 📹 by @modernister for @brickworksbp, shot by @_sirap_⁠. ⁠

#YellowtraceArchitecture #YellowtraceResidential #YellowtraceInterviews #YellowtracePartner #YellowtraceXBrickworks

node.title: Take a tour through La Scala, Richards & Spence's own Brisbane home.

node.text:
✨ Michael Karakolis is the founder and director of @fibonaccistone, Australia. An extremely passionate and dedicated human being, this guy is literally obsessed, and we mean freaking OBSESSED with terrazzo. We thought it was only fitting we got to know the man behind the brand and took a deep dive inside his fascinating brain.
#YellowtraceInterviews #YellowtracePartner #YellowtraceXFibonacci

node.text:
Conceptualized and curated by Dana Tomić Hughes of Yellowtrace, this campaign celebrates the emotive nature of Arflex's iconic and contemporary pieces and the works of some of Australia's most exiting artistic talents. “The concept was about exploring the complementary, yet opposing nature of these uniquely Australian subjects, with the boundary-pushing furniture designs that Arflex is internationally known for.” – Dana Tomić Hughes.

Find out more about this collaboration at https://www.yellowtrace.com.au/yellowtrace-x-arflex-art-design-collaboration-curated-by-dana-tomic-hughes/

node.text:
Do you want to make a positive impact on the environment? The latest sustainable initiative by ⁠⁠
@brickworksbp, Climate Active Certification, is a government-backed program that helps businesses reduce their carbon footprint and prove that they’ve achieved net-zero emissions. Hit the link in bio to learn more. 👊🏻👊🏽👊🏾⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Shown here, in the order of appearance, Australian architecture projects using Daniel Robertson certified carbon neutral bricks from Brickworks. ⁠⁠

Within this three story sandstone corner shop, @ysg.studio has designed an irresistibly indulgent family home. In the main bathroom, the horizontal bands of rose-tinted limestone tiles grant the illusion of sunlight streaming within. Tactical mirror placements visually amplify dimensions and bounce natural light throughout. One of many, these sublime bathrooms are just the tip of the iceberg. Hit the 🔗 in bio for more. 💆🏿💆🏽💆 ⁠⁠

node.text:
Ushering in the future of mobile living, @marianadedelas.studio surprises and delights in a new case study that renews a traditional stone shelter, turning it into a luxurious and airy bijoux dwelling in rural Mallorca. Designed and built in collaboration with @2monos_studio, the hideout’s newly revived structure has been optimised for everyday comforts while a solar panel wheelbarrow utilises the position of the sun to charge the inside. See more via the 🔗 in bio. 🤩⁠⁠

node.text:
Through an elegantly radical palette and flowing interior, @ysg.studio's transformation of the late 19th-century corner shop gives rise to a comfortable and indulgent family home. Retaining the buildings historical essence, the seemingly odd pairing of Art Nouveau elements and Japanese traditions bridge the divide between heritage and contemporary styling, resulting in an entirely new kind of aesthetic. Kudos.⁠ Hit the 🔗 in bio to see the rest. 🔥😍⁠⁠
⁠⁠
📸 @prueruscoe⁠⁠

node.text:
Designed by Beijing-based @clouarchitects, Sanya Farm Lab is a multipurpose infrastructure interlocked with ties between traditional and modern life. Inside the grided façade, inspired by the architecture of the Hainan Li tribe, floors are dotted with microclimates, vertical gardens and agricultural robots encouraging visitor interaction—a reflection of the current population's desire to be in touch with nature once more. See more via the 🔗 in bio 😱⁠⁠
⁠⁠
📸 #shininglabratory⁠⁠

node.text:
Tolomeo, Tizio, Shogun, Demetra — sound familiar? No lighting brand looms quite as large as @artemide_lighting. Since being founded in Milan in 1960 by Ernesto Gismondi, Artemide has been responsible for some of the most iconic pieces of contemporary design. Their collection of world-class pieces is suitable for every room and every need, striking a balance between form, function, innovation and efficiency. Available in Australia exclusively through @stylecraftfurniture⁠ and @stylecraft.home⁠. Hit the 🔗 in bio to see more.💡🥰⁠⁠

Distinctly retro-futuristic, @liang_architecture has balanced soft with hard in this boutique in Hangzhou. A sleek spiral staircase disrupts the imposing brutalist shell. Clad in rich chocolate velvet, its strong hue adds a romantic and dynamic edge to the eternal architecture. ⁠See more via the 🔗 in bio. 💖⁠⁠
